  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two scenarios. Scenario 1 shows three connected carts moving along a track that consists of an elevated middle section with two symmetric sloping sides on either side of it leading to the ground. Scenario 2 shows a sphere moving through a vertical tunnel that passes through the center of a planet. A note states that the figures are not drawn to scale.\" src=\"/images/9827c146234686c340f5f4dd3190d169.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, a system of three connected carts can move along a track that has a flat, horizontal middle section between two sloping sections. In Scenario <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, a metal sphere moves vertically inside a tunnel through a planet of uniform density and with no atmosphere. The tunnel passes through the center of the planet and the sphere remains inside the tunnel. Which of the following correctly indicates which scenario(s), if either, has (have) an equilibrium position and a <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">linear</span> restoring force?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><colgroup><col class=\"colspec colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1\"></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Equilibrium Position</th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Linear Restoring Force</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Both scenarios</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Neither scenario</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Both scenarios</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Scenario 2 only</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Scenario 2 only</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Neither scenario</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Scenario 2 only</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Scenario 2 only</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n",
